The election of John W. Lonsdale as chairman of the board of Pease & Elliman, Inc., a 67‐year‐old realty concern, was announced yesterday by the board of directors. Mr. Lonsdale formerly was vice chairman of Brown, Harris, Stevens, Inc. He is a specialist in residential real estate, particularly cooperative apartments. At Pease & Elliman he Will be responsible for shaping company policy and its activities in the residential field.